name: Starbucks coffee
directions: Enter and the bathrooms are immediately to the right.

name: Del Taco
directions: Right from door

name: Robina Super Center
directions: Up the large stair case in the Center between the two main buildings seen at street view

name: Great Swamp National Wildlife Reserve
directions: Outside of the visitor center
comment: only one stalled bathrooms, almost like an outhouse

name: Clark
comment: Gas station

name: County of Santa Clara Dept. of Child Support Services
directions: enter building, turn left, walk to end of hall.

name: Lory Student Center
directions: Gender neutral restrooms on  all 3 floors

name: Cup A Joe Café
directions: back right of the restaurant, by the back rear entrance. accessible, roomy, and very clean !!!

name: Cup A Joe Café
directions: located in the back right of the restaurant, by the rear entrance to the café. accessible, roomy, and very clean !
comment: you can probably use this whether or not you buy anything, but i recommend their english rose drink !

name: Silver Creek high school
directions: In the nurses office

name: Silver Creek Senior High
directions: In the nurses office

name: North Metropolitan TAFE Building 5
directions: There are 3 bathrooms overall. 2 in the graphic design building at the back, and one in the art building. There are easy signs to follow for the closest one to you.
comment: These bathrooms are for students of this TAFE only, so unless you're a student or a friend of one, don't use these. The bathrooms tend to be very clean.

name: Forrest Chase Shopping Mall
directions: There are 2 stalls next to each other under some escalators that are in front of Bocelli's Espresso Café.
comment:
These are 2 mechanical lifts that have doors similar to those of lifts. Inside the stalls are a toilet seat, a sink, hand drier, soap dispenser and a bin. You are allowed 10 minutes in the stall at a time.

Quality: The stalls are very unsanitary. There was unidentifiable liquid on the floor (either water, urine, or both), there was a bad odour, the surfaces were covered in water, but weren't dirty.

name: Midland Train Station
directions: They are located in the back corner of the building. The building itself is one large room so it's easy to find.
comment: The floor was clean but the environment didn't feel sterile. There is a bad odour and surfaces didn't look properly cleaned.

name: Inkwell Coffee House
comment: There are two gender neutral single stall restrooms. This is one of the only places I feel safe using the restroom.

name: Midland Gate
directions: There are at least 3-4 unisex/disabled, male, and female bathrooms within the shopping centre. There are signs and maps that show where the bathrooms are.

name: Taco Bell
directions: Next to the entrance
comment: I believe you have to be a customer to use it

name: Westminster Mall
directions: Inside the mall, bottom floor, right in front of JcPenny's and next to the kids' play area

name: Kazza Wine Bar
directions: Straight to the back of the bar
comment: Customers only, but it's a decently sized single-user restroom.

name: Bahama Buck's
directions: Right in the back

name: Mezzo Cafe
directions: In the back, on the way to the patio.

name: Goodwill
directions: Go straight to the back of the store
comment: It's labeled as "All Gender" and includes a toilet and a urinal

name: Alexandria Visitor Centre
directions: Lowest floor, stairs are on the right from main entrance and a side entrance opens to the lower floor
comment: Very low ceilings

name: Urgent Care Center
comment: Ask to use bathroom first, it's Very Clean

name: Illinois Masonic Surgical Waiting Room
directions: So, I know it's on the third floor of a hospital, specifically in the OR waiting room, but it's available. There's two single still bathrooms right here and one of them is labelled gender neutral, the other is not.

name: Blick art supplies store
directions: Straight to the back wall

name: Cherry Hill Village Theater
directions: Near back entrance, another in the lounge.
comment: Only accessible during shows or rehearsals.

name: Cat's Protection Adoption Center
directions: Walk through reception into cat holding/viewing area and it is the first door on the left.
comment: Possibly need to sign in at the desk (especially if you want to see the cats, since that's the usual procedure) but if you just tell the receptionist that you need to use the bathroom they will probably let you go through without signing in.

name: Anna's Taqueria
directions: To the left in the back
comment: They usually let you use if you ask.

name: Punch
directions: Access via the courtyard at the back
comment: The restroom is more accessible from outside via the back alley. Punch has great food and service.

name: The Chieftan Pub
directions: In the back past the bar are 2 restrooms that used to be male/female but are now have signs on the door designating them as gender neutral.
comment: The pub itself is small and crowded with tables/stools and may cause problems for someone in chair or with mobility issues trying to get to the restrooms -  even though at least one of the restrooms (the one previously designated for women) is large and has assistance bars on the wall.

name: The Truffle Table
directions: Walk around the bar, and there are two single stall, gender neutral restrooms on the left of the hall. Pads, tampons and changing tables provided.
comment: The restaurant is seat yourself so just pretend like you're finding a table.

name: The Eagle
directions: Back of the building, to the left

name: Moo & Brew
directions: walk straight in, turn to your right, then left behind a wall.
comment: they likely won't question whether or not you're a customer, the staff is all cool. I'd recommend eating here too if you're looking for a meal in a place that you can pee!

name: Saz's Miller High Life Pavilion, State Fair Park
directions: back corner of the pavilion behind one of the black curtains
comment: ask an employee to use the bathroom as it is the employees' restroom, in all likelihood they will say yes, sazs is a trans friendly compnay

name: Sangria 46
directions: Passed the bar, on the right hand side.
comment: 2 single stall gender neutral bathrooms. Hope I labled this right.

name: Milwaukee Brat House
directions: First floor, straight back, on the thought together right

name: Roots cafe
directions: Not accessible, restaurant has lots of stairs
comment: Paying customer only

name: Donde la bandera de italia (no recuerdo el nombre)
Donde la bandera de italia (no recuerdo el nombre)
directions: Al fondo del bar

name: Los Angeles State Historic Park
directions: The building that houses the multipurpose room near the park's south entrance also has about half a dozen unisex, single-stall restrooms.
comment: Restrooms are only open during the park's operating hours and on quiet days, not all the stalls are opened for use.

name: Espresso Royale
comment: Laid back coffee shop. In an emergency, you could probably slip in unnoticed as it's not within view of register.

name: Grandma's House
directions: Two non-labelled rooms at the back right corner.
comment: Depending on how busy it is you could just walk right to it. The bar is to the left when you enter.

name: McDonald's
directions: Once you get to the drinks, make a left into the play place. It's directly straight from the door towards the back. One of the two stalls is for small children, but the other one is normal.

name: Starbucks
directions: through the main entrance the restrooms are all the way to the right, but there's a side entrance that opens directly to the restroom doors that's more discreet
comment: if you're just using the bathrooms, use the side doors and employees won't even see you

name: Starbucks
directions: All the way back
comment: They'd prefer it if you bought something, but don't enforce it

name: Sincerely Yogurt
directions: Back wall, left side

name: Battlestaff Games
directions: Upstairs on either side
comment: They're support cool, love these guys.

name: Grad Cru
directions: Inside in back of establishment

name: Central Market
directions: In cafeteria, right side of building
comment: Family restroom

name: Oak Lawn Coffee
directions: To the left of the entrance, across from the counter/cash register.

name: Whole Foods market
directions: In the corner near the bar/resturant area
comment: Have to be a customer

name: Urban Outfitters
directions: ask staff to unlock the bathroom
comment: act like you're browsing for a bit

name: Louie's Wine Dive - Broad Ripple
directions: By the kitchen

name: Starbucks
directions: Toilets located up stairs inside shop.
comment: Single stalls Male, Female, Disabled and Gender-Neutral - may need to ask staff to unlock.

name: Starbucks
street: 1, Touchwood Court, 12 High St, Solihull B91 3TB
directions: Starbucks located outside Touch wood,  toilets accessible on second floor up the stairs inside Starbucks.
comment: Single stalls Male, Female, Disabled, Gender Neutral. If unlocked ask at the till. May need to purchase something.

name: Starbucks
street: 1, Touchwood Court, 12 High St, Solihull B91 3TB
directions: Starbucks outside torchwood, head up the stairs. Single Male and Female stall, single 'disabled' stall, and single Gender Neutral stall.
comment: If locked, ask a member of staff to unlock for you - may need to purchase something.

name: Yogurtland
directions: To the left of the store

name: Fig's Beanery & Creamery
directions: To the left of the front counter past the "Pantry" sign through the beaded curtains that says "outhouse" and it's straight on the right.
comment: Public restroom. Staff is nice.

name: Aki Japanese Cuisine
directions: At the back of the restaurant
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Bryan Street Tavern
comment: Theres a neon sign above bathrooms indicating that both rooms are for "women" in a joking manner. Theyre essentially gender neutral.

name: Chevron
directions: Restrooms are located along the right side of the gas station store. There are 4 all gender restrooms.

name: Burger King
directions: As soon as you walk in the door turn right and you will see the restroom

name: Maverik
directions: Only one floor, in far left corner.

name: McDonald's
directions: Go through the entrance and turn to your right. There is a single stall unisex restroom as well as gendered restrooms.

name: Starbucks
directions: The store is drive-thu/ walk up only, so the bathroom is outside near the walk-up window
comment:
You have to ask the person at the walk-up window to open the door for you, but their policy is to do so even if you are not a customer. Just be polite and don't go immediately before close
t

name: Urban Skillet
comment: Customers only

name: Museum of Modern Art
directions: By the coat racks and the tickets past the courtyard
comment: There is Self Identified Men's, Self Identified Women's, and Family that are all accessible. They're open to public.

name: Souvlaki GR Midtown
directions: Back hallway by the kitchens on the left
comment: They expect you to eat there if you use it. It's also a shop so just look around a little and you should be able to use it without being stopped.

name: Cabela's
directions:
Turn leftt when you first enter from the from the main entrance and you should see a big restroom sign.

When you enter turn left like you're going to go to the women's side but then on the left hand side before you reach the women's restroom you'll see a family restroom, there it is.

name: That Crepe Place
comment: It's a small bakery, so you may have to buy something

name: Waterville Opera House
directions: Up the stairs on the left side of the building.
comment: Large and clean

name: The General American Donut Company
directions: Left side walking in - can't miss the neon sign from the counter
comment:
Hours Tues-Fri 6:30am- 1pm
Sat, Sun 7:30-1pm

name: Gaithersburg Arts Barn
directions:
two spacious, clean gender neutral restrooms. three ways to get there:
1) ask for the elevator key that will let you access level S, go up and go right of the ladders when you get out. this way is accessible/ requires no stairs. 
2) go up the stairs and in through the green door to the right of the elevator. 
3) go up the stairs and in through the theatre doors, then through the green door on the stage-left side backstage.

name: Gaithersburg Arts Barn
directions: second floor, backstage. you can either go through the green door to the right of the elevator, or you can walk across the stage and use the green door next to the sound board on the stage left side and then turn left. two spacious, clean, single-stall gender neutral dressing rooms with a toilet/sink each.

name: The beauty mark
directions: In the back
comment: Very friendly, just say you need a restroom

name: The beauty mark
directions: In the back of the store
comment: They're friendly to trans here, especially Kandice

name: Circle K on highway 30
directions: It's by the fountain drinks, semi hidden but very clean.
comment: Can use condoms in bathroom for makeshift packers, also lots of food to snack on. There are 2 on highway 30 set up the same

name: Sterling State Park
directions: By the parking lot for swimming in the lake. Each single bathroom in the building is all-gender.
comment: You have to have a Michigan State park pass. Open 8-10, at least in summer. Not all have changing tables, but some do.

name: I81 n ext. 80 flyn j truck stop.
comment: The staff doesnt bother u u can go in and pee or poo. ..good place if ur heading this way.
